text:
I got something like that for testRedirector5 to 12 and testRedirector14 under
win2000 and cygwin. Looks like a whitespace difference, not sure.

ExecuteOnTest	testRedirect5	Failure	unexpected output expected:<blah y z[ x blah
z x y blah] > but was:<blah y z[ x blah z x y blah ] >

I also get a failure for testRedirector14.  ;)  Are you using the cygwin svn
client or the Windows one?  I am becoming suspicious of EOL-related failures on
cygwin; they were making InputTest fail for me.  I am unclear, though, whether
the cygwin behavior comes from ANY newer version of subversion, just the cygwin
version, or just the cygwin version on systems that have \n configured as the
default cygwin EOL (like I have).
